 ,(598,'<p>Bitcoin has done well in the past because of its novelty. Spectators excited about the worlds first decentralized digital currency eagerly entered into the market, and by doing so drove up the value of the currency. But now the rush appears to have ended.</p>\r\n<p><br />In order for the value of bitcoin to remain steady, the bitcoin community will have to find new uses for the currency. Bitcoin holders may no longer be able to rely on speculation to keep the price of their money high. New, alternative sources of activity that will attract people to the currency are now required.</p>\r\n<p><br />Thus, bitcoin may need to become popular for use in e-commerce. This is already starting to happen. Just in the past few months, several major online businesses accepting bitcoin have opened up. But this is just a start. More bitcoin businesses are needed, and these businesses will need the support of the community to remain financially afloat.</p>\r\n<p><br />Bitcoins have great potential. But innovation is required to realize the dream of a truly decentralized, Internet based currency.</p>')
